Text: I have only one an hour to write this post.
It is the first time when I left the blog for the last minute, but it sometimes does.
I have spent almost the whole weekend to learn HTMLÂ  and CSS for INFO202 - to improve the style of the project which I prepare.
I feel like a turtle or a snail.
Everything takes me to much time.
Maybe that is why I feel a little bit resigned.
I focus on these studies, but the rest of my life is somewhere away.
Again I have to manoeuvre between my family, some stuff in Poland and studies.
Life was supposed to be more comfortable in the next three months because we had a plan that my mum will come to us and take over my kids during my exams and placement.
COVID-19 thwarted all the plans.
And now, more specific information: Â Â  Â We had a meeting in a hospital last week with more persons from the hospital side.
Each next conversation shows us some new facts we have to deal with it.
But on the other hand, it is very crucial for us.
Off course we will focus on the essential aspects - their priorities.
The rest will be for the next project.
I think that they are very excited to get some automation and I hope we can deliver it at least in part of it.
But I know that we do not have enough time to provide the full solution.
Everything takes a long time - especially me.
We had our joint meeting twice to discuss the tasks or next steps and code together for a few hours.
It helps me to understand the whole process, and I don't have to struggle with a bug for the next few hours on my own.
Somebody always knows how to fix it.
My teammates are more familiar with the coding and understand all single part.
And I am grateful that they want to share with me their knowledge.
I wasn't involved too much in the coding of our project last week.
I tried to catch up on my individual project and understand more about team project during our meetings.
Gogo took over our part (mine and Gogo's )last week.
Now it is quite a boring part to describe in the blog - because it is only coding, but more exciting for the team.
We see the progress, and it is something for what each of us waits and expects.
Our goals for last week were: 1/ Meeting with the client - to receive feedback on the UI part of our project - it ran smoothly, and we got more tips.
2/ Coding, coding, and coding again - this is this boring part for you.
We are using models in WPF to display data (Presentation Patterns:  MVC, MVP, PM, MVVM).
https: //www.simform.com/mvc-mvp-mvvm-ios-app-development/.
3/ Merge all parts (DB, APP and UI) - methods and models.
Teams goals for next week: 1/ Meeting with the client - to show progress.
2/ Coding - again.
My individual goals: 1/ Finish the milestone INF0202.
And start to prepare for the blackboard test, which will be in the week of our final presentation.
2/ Start to prepare portfolio - I don't have to much hope, that I will do this in this week.
Anyway, I will try. It is still something abstractive for me.
Thank you, and have a lovely week.
